This program finds the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) of two numbers. It checks all possible divisors using a loop. The largest common divisor is stored in a variable. After checking all values, the GCD is displayed.
[ C++ Practice Test ]
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;int main() {
int a = 24, b = 36, gcd = 1;
for (int i = 1; i <= a && i <= b; i++) {
if (a % i == 0 && b % i == 0)
gcd = i;
}
cout << "GCD = " << gcd;
return 0;
}
Output :
GCD = 12
